   stands for the wave function of the universe. 
The operator 
  
    
      
        
          
            
              H
              ^
            
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\hat {H}}}
   acts on the Hilbert space of wave
functions, but it is not the same Hilbert space as in the nonrelativistic case. This Hamiltonian no longer determines the evolution of the system because the Schrödinger equation: 
  
    
      
        
          
            
              H
              ^
            
          
        
        
          |
        
